Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on learning the policy of an inquiry dialog system, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of deep reinforcement learning (DRL) to learn the inquiry dialog policies is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the domain of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a recursive neural network (RNN) for logical formula embedding, which is a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the development of an inquiry dialog system, which involves software engineering principles and practices. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The use of DRL and RNNs in the paper falls under the domain of neural and evolutionary computing.
